2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .article_excerpt blockquote override
  (strip quote-icon background/padding and inline margins) so the homepage hero
  teaser renders blockquote-led post summaries as normal flowing text instead of
  a narrow, tall column.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added margin-bottom to paragraphs inside
  .article_excerpt blockquote to restore the visual gap between a quoted line and
  its attribution line in the hero teaser (previously only provided by .post p
  padding on the full post page).
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added, then later removed, a
  .lg-outer .lg-thumb-outer padding-top !important override intended to add space
  between the displayed image and the lightGallery thumbnail strip. Superseded by
  the allowMediaOverlap fix below; removed because it was offsetting individual
  thumbnail images down within their boxes.
2026-07-05 - layouts/partials/footer.html: Changed lightGallery's allowMediaOverlap
  option from true to false so the displayed image is sized to leave room for the
  caption and thumbnail strip, stacked without overlapping (title now appears below
  the image and above the thumbnails).
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-thumb-item img { margin: 0; }
  override to fix a pre-existing bug (present in production) where the site's
  global `img { margin: 15px auto; }` rule in _base.scss was pushing lightGallery
  thumbnail images down within their fixed-height, overflow-hidden boxes, leaving a
  blank band at the top of every thumbnail.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-outer .lg-sub-html
  { padding-top: 25px; } to add breathing room between the displayed image and
  its caption (tried 5px first, too subtle; 25px confirmed as the right amount).
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-outer .lg-sub-html
  { color: var(--dark); } so the caption text (previously light gray/white,
  #eee from vendor CSS) is readable now that the backdrop is white.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-container .lg-backdrop
  { background-color: #fff; } to change the gallery's full-screen backdrop
  from black to white, overriding the vendored rule via a more specific
  selector (no !important, no vendor file edits).
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added .lg-container .lg-outer
  .lg-thumb-outer { background-color: #fff; } to match the thumbnail strip's
  background to the new white backdrop, same higher-specificity technique.
2026-07-05 - Investigated why the thumbnail show/hide toggle button
  disappeared after the allowMediaOverlap change: the vendor plugin
  (lg-thumbnail.umd.js) explicitly disables toggleThumb whenever
  allowMediaOverlap is false, since toggling wouldn't resize the image with
  overlap off anyway. Decision: keep allowMediaOverlap: false and live without
  the toggle button rather than reintroduce the caption/image overlap. No code
  change made.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Added a responsive
  .lg-container .lg-outer .lg-img-wrap override (left/right: 15px, width:
  calc(100% - 30px) by default; 80px/calc(100% - 160px) from 768px width up)
  so the displayed image can never grow wide enough to sit directly under the
  prev/next arrow buttons, with a smaller inset on phones so the image isn't
  overly cramped.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_components.scss: Restyled the prev/next buttons
  (.lg-container .lg-next / .lg-prev) to remove the vendor's gray box
  background/padding/border-radius, enlarged the arrow glyph, and set its
  color to var(--dark) (var(--theme) on hover) so they read as plain arrows
  against the white backdrop instead of barely-legible gray rectangles.
2026-07-05 - layouts/shortcodes/gallery.html: Added support for an opt-in
  `break: true` field on an imglist entry, which emits an empty
  .post_gallery_break div right after that thumbnail.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_posts.scss: Added .post_gallery_break { flex-basis:
  100%; height: 0; }, a zero-height full-width flex item that forces the post
  gallery's thumbnail grid to start a new row at that point, giving manual
  control over how many thumbnails appear per row.
2026-07-05 - assets/scss/_posts.scss: Added a scoped `.post ul { list-style:
  disc; padding: 1rem 1.25rem 1rem 2.25rem; }` rule so markdown bullet lists
  in post content (e.g. content/post/jazz-adjacent.md) display their bullets
  again. The global `ul { list-style: none; }` reset in _base.scss (meant for
  nav menus) was stripping them; `ol` already had an equivalent post-scoped
  padding override but `ul` did not.
2026-07-07 - layouts/shortcodes/exhibit.html: New shortcode, modeled on
  gallery.html, for posts that want their on-page images shown at the wider
  -0450.jpg resolution instead of gallery's -0240.jpg thumbnail. Reuses
  gallery's id='lightgallery' and lightbox href/data-srcset so the existing
  lightGallery init code and CSS keep working unchanged.
2026-07-07 - layouts/shortcodes/exhibit.html + assets/scss/_posts.scss: Gave
  exhibit its own post_exhibit / post_exhibit_break classes (previously
  reused gallery's post_gallery / post_gallery_break) and a matching
  &_exhibit block in _posts.scss, so its layout could diverge from
  gallery.html's without touching gallery's CSS. Container capped at
  max-width: 930px !important, with each thumbnail <a> forced to
  calc(50% - 1rem) width (two per row, with a 1rem gap) and its <img> scaled
  to width: 100% of that column.
2026-07-07 - layouts/shortcodes/exhibit.html + assets/scss/_posts.scss: Added
  an opt-in `small: true` field for imglist entries, matching the existing
  `break: true` convention. Flagged entries get class='small' on their <a>,
  overridden in CSS to calc(33.33% - 1rem) width, letting three small images
  sit side by side within the same 930px container that otherwise shows two
  full-width images per row. (Briefly tried widening the container to 1410px
  to fit three full-width images per row, and separately tried scaling the
  default/small anchor widths to 33.33%/18.15% for that wider container, but
  a higher-level layout div constrains the available width, so both of those
  changes were reverted back to max-width: 930px and the default 50% anchor
  width; only the small-image width setting was kept, changed to
  calc(33.33% - 1rem) so three small images fill a 930px row.)
